article.headline: Lehigh 75, Yale 69
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Freshman C.J. McCollum scored a season-high 31 points, including seven 3-pointers, to lead Lehigh to a 75-69 win over Yale on Tuesday night. McCollum was 12-for-18 from the field and 7-for-10 from long range for the Mountain Hawks (9-6), who have won five games in a row. The Bulldogs (4-11) have lost five straight. Lehigh led by as many as eight points in the first half before trailing 33-32 at halftime. The score was tied four times in the second half, the last at 45 with 13:16 left. Over the next 2:40, the Mountain Hawks used an 11-1 run, capped by a McCollum 3-pointer, to lead 56-46. Yale never got closer than six points the rest of the game. Zahir Carrington added 16 points for Lehigh and Marquis Hall had a career-high 11 assists. Michael Sands had 17 points and Greg Mangano added 14 points and 13 rebounds for the Bulldogs, who outrebounded Lehigh 47-35.
